m","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"William I Pitkin was born in 1465, in Devon, England, United Kingdom. He had at least 1 daughter with Alice Agnes. He died in 1510, in his hometown, at the age of 45."},"et":{"1465–1510":"1465–1510","1470–1510":"1470–1510","1486–1548":"1486–1548","1510":"1510","1465":"1465","1486":"1486","1470":"1470","1548":"1548","Devon England":"Devon, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Devon, England":"Devon, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1465–1510":"1465–1510","1470–1510":"1470–1510","1486–1548":"1486–1548","1510":"1510","1465":"1465","1486":"1486","1470":"1470","1548":"1548","Devon England":"Devon, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Devon, England":"Devon, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1465–1510":"1465–1510","1470–1510":"1470–1510","1486–1548":"1486–1548","1510":"1510","1465":"1465","1486":"1486","1470":"1470","1548":"1548","Devon England":"Devon, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Devon, England":"Devon, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"William I Pitkin est né en 1465, à Devon, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Il a eu au moins 1 fille avec Alice Agnes. Il est décédé en 1510, dans sa ville natale, à l’âge de 45 ans."},"de":{"1465–1510":"1465–1510","1470–1510":"1470–1510","1486–1548":"1486–1548","1510":"1510","1465":